parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause damage to the engine, lead to overheating, and potentially cause a fire hazard.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the intake manifold gasket
pinion seal
valve cover
and other engine components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system failures can cause engine overheating, damage to engine components, and potentially lead to engine failure.
symptoms: Coolant leaks
overheating
false instrument readings
and gumming up of the thermostat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: Engine failure
engine cutting out
and difficulty starting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Spark plug and wire issues can cause engine misfires, difficulty starting the vehicle, and decreased engine performance.
symptoms: Engine misfires
difficulty starting the vehicle
and spark plug and wire failures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Air intake system failures can cause engine performance issues, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine damage.
symptoms: Air leaks from the intake manifold
air intake boot failures
and oxygen sensor failures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system issues can cause engine stalling, difficulty starting the vehicle, and potentially lead to safety risks.
symptoms: Engine cutting out when the hood gets wet
and electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brakes can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear brakes do not engage or release properly
causing uneven wear on the brake pads
loud squealing noises
and a "not smooth" stopping feel. The rear wheels may continue to turn even when the brake pedal is pressed
and the vehicle may slide or lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal may feel soft or spongy
and the brakes may not engage or release properly
causing uneven wear on the brake pads and rotors. The brakes may also make loud noises
such as grinding or squealing
when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS brakes may grind or make loud noises
causing failure of the braking system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear on the brake rotors can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake rotors may warp or crack prematurely
causing uneven wear on the brake pads and affecting the overall braking performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants are not adequately protected.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a collision
despite meeting the deployment criteria
resulting in occupant injuries or fatalities.
